title: Hear A-Trak's Diverse 'Cut it Out!' Mix With Kanye West, Paul Simon
text:
A-Trak has unveiled Cut it Out! , a 74-minute DJ mix featuring a diverse array of artists, including Kanye West, Justin Timberlake, Paul Simon, A Tribe Called Quest, Rage Against the Machine, Nine Inch Nails and many others. Related PHOTOS: 50 Most Important People in EDM The movers, shakers and speaker-quakers shaping dance in 2014 
The 54-track set opens with a mashup of Kanye West's "Can't Tell Me Nothing" and Jean-Luc Ponty's "Don't Let the World Pass You By." Later in the lively mix at around the 44:00 mark, Paul Simon's "The Werewolf" features on a track named "Stranger" with Nico Segal and Nate Fox, and Nine Inch Nails and Danny Brown are interpolated on "Becoming a Blunt" at around the 48:15 mark. Cut it Out! caps off with Vince Staples'"Big Time" and A Tribe Called Quest's "Solid Wall of Sound." 
Last fall, A-Trak released the retrospective LP In the Loop: Decades of Remixes on his own Fool's Gold label.
